Volcano plot Thin vs Early Biofilm
This plot shows a moderate but well‑defined differential expression pattern, with distinct clusters of significantly upregulated and downregulated genes separating cleanly along the fold‑change axis. 
The horizontal spread indicates measurable shifts in expression magnitude between the two stages, while the vertical distribution reflects strong statistical support for many of these changes.
Although the overall signal is less extensive than in the Mature vs Early contrast, the plot still highlights a substantial set of genes whose expression differs significantly as cells transition from early biofilm formation into the thin biofilm state. This distribution underscores the presence of coordinated transcriptional adjustments during this intermediate stage.
Biologically, this pattern reflects the early stages of the metabolic and stress‑response shift, where thin biofilm cells begin reducing glycolytic and growth‑associated activity while initiating partial activation of oxidative‑stress and mitochondrial pathways as they adapt to the wine‑surface environment.

