Volcano Plot Thin vs Mature Biofilm
This plot  shows a strong and well‑defined differential expression pattern, with clear clusters of significantly upregulated and downregulated genes separating along the fold‑change axis. 
The broad horizontal spread reflects substantial changes in expression magnitude between the two stages, while the tall vertical distribution indicates high statistical confidence for many of these differences. 
Compared with the Thin vs Early contrast, the signal here is more extensive, highlighting the large transcriptional shift that occurs as the biofilm completes its transition into the mature state. 
Biologically, this distribution reflects the full activation of late‑stage metabolic and stress‑response programs in mature biofilm, alongside the decline of intermediate‑stage signatures that remain more prominent in thin biofilm.
